commit.message:
Add licence to opam file

Also remove spurious src address

Remove build mark on dune dependency in .opam file

This is in general incorrect as dune generate some files
Point to the real documentation URL
Point to 1.1 in the OPAM file
Build the doc in the opam file
Add a small note on for home testing
Oups bytes was not really tested...
Test: fix bad test on big endian architectures
CI: use explicit version numbers in the travis setup

mark cppo as a build dependency

via @TheLortex in mirage/mirage#969

port to dune, upgrade opam metadata and remove unused code

- removed vestigial ocamlbuild files (_tags)
- port to dune (as dune 1.7 will issue jbuild deprecation warnings)
- upgrade opam metadata to the 2.0 format
- remove ocaml <4.01 support, as minimum version is now ocaml 4.02+
- restore -inline 1000 to build rules (dropped with jbuilder port)

Bump version to 1.0

This has been stable for long enough.
And regenerate oasis files.
